# Observability contract — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

How and what to log. Adding a log site consults this file.

## Levels

| Level | Use for | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| error | failures the user/operator must know | failed persistence |
| warn | recoverable anomalies | retry, fallback used |
| info | significant lifecycle events | session started |
| debug | development detail | dev only, off in release |

## Rules
- Never log secrets, tokens, or PII (`docs/database/storage-boundaries.md`).
- Log at the boundary where a Failure is produced/translated, not everywhere it passes.
- Use structured fields, not string concatenation, for machine-readable logs.
